</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_454" id="226v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Hansen <expan>vo<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>Liechtenst<ex>ein</ex></expan>, <expan>gesezze<ex>n</ex></expan> czü
                        Czetmesstorf </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab>Lieber Hans, als ir uns <expan>v<ex>er</ex>schrib<ex>e</ex>n</expan> habt,
                        wie ew <expan>fürkume<ex>n</ex></expan> sey, daz wir ew in beschuldigung
                                <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> süllen, <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
                        wir <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan> brief wol <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nomen</expan>
                        und wissen czü der czeit davon nichts. Wer es aber, daz ew
                                <expan>dhein<ex>er</ex></expan> der <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
                        iht beschuldigt, den lieszt <add>uns</add> mit namen wissen, so
                                <expan>wolt<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir sein red
                            <expan>hör<ex>e</ex>n</expan> und ew <expan>dan<ex>n</ex></expan>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> ein antwurt <expan>wisse<ex>n</ex></expan>
                            lassen.<expan> Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> vi <expan>an<ex>te</ex></expan>
<expan>Walp<ex>ur</ex>g<ex>en</ex></expan>.</ab>
</div>
